For a specific region of interest, the probability, pi, of mutation in tumor i is a function of the length of that region and the expected mutation rates of individual nucleotides in that region under the null hypothesis. Assuming qi, j is the mutation probability of nucleotide j in tumor i, and l is the length of the region of interest:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
