The expected fraction of hotspot (or non-hotspot) mutations in the functional region type (p2) is the fraction of the genome that constitutes the functional region. The observed fraction of hotspot (or non-hotspot) mutations in the functional region is calculated by adding all mutations in the functional region type and dividing by the total number of mutations genome-wide (p1). The log odds ratio of the enrichment of hotspot (or non-hotspot) mutations in a functional region type is given by,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
